    "title": "Moody's Upgrades Cyprus to A3 With a Stable Outlook as Government Debt Shrinks - MarketScreener",
    "text": "By Stephen Nakrosis\nMoody's Ratings said it was upgrading Cyprus to A3 from Baa2, as the nation continues to lower its fiscal and debt metrics.\nCyprus has significantly reduced its government debt ratio since its peak in 2020, Moody's said Friday, ranking among the countries with the largest debt ratio reductions globally.\nMoody's said it expects the debt ratio will continue to decline over the medium term, while debt affordability metrics are expected to remain favorable.\nCyprus' medium-term economic outlook is solid, driven by the steady expansion of high-productivity services sectors, Moody's said.\nThe country has a stable outlook, reflecting a balance of risks related to economic, fiscal and debt prospects, Moody's said.\nThe agency expects banking sector risks will remain contained given the material strengthening of the credit profiles of Cypriot banks in recent years.\nWrite to Stephen Nakrosis at stephen.nakrosis@wsj.com\n(END) Dow Jones Newswires\n11-22-24 1805ET\nShare © Dow Jones - 2024",
